main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified aerial phenomena (UAP) were reported in Decatur, Nebraska on December 20, 1955, involving various objects with unique characteristics and maneuvers witnessed over the course of several hours.
interesting points: Sightings included winged-shaped objects with red, blue, green, and white lights moving at great speeds
Objects were observed to move rapidly, stop, hover, and then accelerate away at high rates of speed
Witness reported seeing circular, metallic, glowing objects with pulsating orange lights hovering over a farm for about 3 minutes before moving away
Description of the objects included unique and unusual characteristics such as sudden spreading of wings and glowing trailing edges
The witness provided an estimated speed of 50 m.p.h. and an estimated distance of 1,000 feet for one of the observed objects
sighted object: Multiple unidentified objects with unique shapes and lights
witnesses: Multiple witnesses including the person who completed the questionnaire at Parks Air Force Base, California
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
